<P>
   CAMBODIA-DEFECTORS (Phnom Penh) _ Hun Sen, the Cambodian leader,
responding to criticism for his statement that defecting Khmer
Rouge leaders should be met with bouquets rather than handcuffs,
says he is in favor of punishing them, but that it is the province
of the courts to decide. Earlier, a Khmer Rouge spokesman suggests
putting the U.S. on trial for its bombing of Cambodia. By Seth
Mydans. With map.
</P>
