   EURO (Frankfurt, Germany) _ Thursday was a day for champagne and
confetti. Friday began the long weekend of strong coffee and
takeout food as financial institutions in Europe began the daunting
job of re-programming their electronic networks for the euro era
before the markets open for business on Monday. By Edmund L.
Andrews.
</P>
