   COP-ARREST (Seattle) _ An off duty police officer is arrested
for vehicular homicide after a 3 a.m. New Year's Day accident.
Police say he was drunk, and speeding. Acknowledging that all
Washington state cops just completed training in the new DUI laws,
cops at the scene say, ``We didn't set a good example.''
</P>
<P>
   By Jack Hopkins. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
