<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-COTTON-GAMER-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TEXAS POUNDS MISSISSIPPI STATE BEHIND APPLEWHITE, WILLIAMS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MIKE JONES 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   DALLAS _ By the time Ricky got his groove back, the Longhorns
were already in one.
</P>
<P>
   Texas' Heisman Trophy-winning back Ricky Williams burst out of
the fog for 104 yards, including touchdown runs of 37 and two
yards, to lead Texas to 24 points and the record for the most
productive third quarter in Southwestern Bell Cotton Bowl history.
</P>
<P>
   Williams finished with a Texas bowl-rushing-record 203 yards on
30 carries and caught five passes for 45 more yards, earning him
honors as offensive player of the game. But the groundwork for
Texas' 38-11 victory against Mississippi State before a crowd of
72,611 had already been laid through the air and in the trenches.
</P>
<P>
   On the way to a 14-3 halftime lead, the Longhorns' surprising
defense, led by linebacker Aaron Babino, had withstood the best
that MSU tailback James Johnson had to offer. Though Johnson gained
105 of 122 yards in the first half, the Bulldogs reached no deeper
than the UT 22.
</P>
<P>
   And in the meantime, Texas quarterback Major Applewhite and wide
receiver Wane McGarity had taken measure of the best pass defense
in the Southeastern Conference. Applewhite and McGarity connected
for first-half touchdown passes of 59 and 52 yards. And those jabs
set the Bulldogs up for Williams' knockout punches.
</P>
<P>
   ``Those touchdown passes did a few things,'' said Texas coach
Mack Brown, whose Longhorns rose to 9-3 by winning Texas' first New
Year's Day bowl since defeating Alabama here in 1982.
</P>
<P>
   ``Obviously, they had to try to slow Ricky down and rattle
Major. That has to be the plan if you're going to play us. When
Major hit the two big balls \Rto McGarity\S and the other screen
\Rto Kwame Cavil\S that was so close to a touchdown, I felt like
that gave him the confidence that he could play against their
defense.
</P>
<P>
   ``And then when they had to slow down their blitzes some, Ricky
made the big plays in the third quarter.''
</P>
<P>
   After his 37-yard scoring run put Texas up 21-3 less than three
minutes into the second half, Williams struck the Heisman pose his
teammates have been after him all year to do. The end-zone antic
cost Texas a 15-yard unsportsmanlike penalty on the kickoff, but to
no damage.
</P>
<P>
   ``I felt like we had a big enough lead that the penalty wouldn't
hurt us,'' Williams said, sporting a sheepish grin.
</P>
<P>
   The youthful but poised Applewhite completed 15 of 26 passes for
225 yards and three TDs _ including an 18-yard strike to Cavil with
14 seconds left in the record-setting third quarter that gave Texas
a 38-3 lead.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's no question that Major did a great job,'' said MSU
coach Jackie Sherrill. ``He did a great job of getting the ball
where it was supposed to be. But you can't give Major all the
credit because he had some help.''
</P>
<P>
   McGarity's ability to get deep against a defense that prepped to
prevent such occurrences, loomed large. He caught four passes for
132 yards.
</P>
<P>
   ``They play a defense that takes a lot of chances,'' McGarity
said. ``We took advantage of that and made it a weakness.''
</P>
<P>
   Applewhite _ the focus of MSU's defense _ was sacked only once
behind an offensive line that picked up and discarded almost every
blitz and stunt.
</P>
<P>
   ``Their offensive line was real tight with their splits,'' said
MSU defensive end Edward Smith, who had 12 sacks this season, none
yesterday. ``We weren't able to get the penetration we needed.''
</P>
<P>
   Applewhite became one of four quarterbacks to throw three TD
passes in a Cotton Bowl game.
</P>
<P>
   ``If I had to put a word on this season, it would be historic,''
he said. ``You end a 47-game \Rhome\S winning streak \Rat
Nebraska\S. Ricky winning the Heisman and all the rushing records
he broke. The season has been historical and at the same time
magical. It is a great moment for Texas.''
</P>
<P>
   The victory was Brown's first in a New Year's bowl and iced a
magical first season at Texas, which should move up from its No. 20
ranking in the final Associated Press poll.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think we've become one of the best teams in the country, and
I hope the ratings show that when they come out after the national
championship game,'' Brown said.
</P>
<P>
   ``Today was very special for us for a lot of reasons. We were
not champions of the Big 12 or the Big 12 South, so we felt this
was the only way we could become champions and we did that today.
Also, it was important for us to win a major bowl game because we
had not won one since 1982. It's been a great season.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
