<HEADLINE>
SPOTLIGHT KILLS LOUISIANA WOMAN CELEBRATING NEW YEAR'S 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  (Attn: Louisiana) 
 
By S.K. BARDWELL 
c.1998 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON _ A woman celebrating New Year's died in a hotel lobby
early Friday when a 200-pound spotlight fell on her from the fourth
floor.
</P>
<P>
   Tracy Guy, 33, of Kenner, La., was walking through the lobby of
the Hyatt Regency in downtown Houston when a spotlight used in the
hotel's celebration crushed her.
</P>
<P>
   Guy was rushed to Ben Taub Hospital, where she was pronounced
dead from her injuries.
</P>
<P>
   Guy's companion, 27-year-old James Lutz of Luling, La., was
treated for a contusion to his left foot and released later.
</P>
<P>
   Two Houston party-goers, Kimberly Vega, 32, and Haytham
Alkhaldi, 26, also were treated for contusions suffered in the
accident.
</P>
<P>
   The spotlight, one of two mounted on a fourth-floor ledge, was
being removed by workers with, LD Systems Inc., a company that
provides equipment for special events when it fell, police said.
</P>
<P>
   The accident occurred as the hotel's party was finishing up.
Witnesses said there were fewer than 100 people left in the lobby
area when the spotlight fell or more people would have been hurt.
</P>
<P>
   Police said when a sandbag was removed from the light's base, it
became too heavy for another worker to hold, and it toppled over
the ledge.
</P>
<P>
   A hotel spokesman Friday called the death ``very sad,'' but
referred questions about the incident to police.
</P>
<P>
   Houston homicide investigators, many of whom were working extra
jobs at the hotel for the New Year's party, were looking into Guy's
death but said there was no indication it was anything other than a
tragic accident.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
XXXX END OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
