<SLUG> BC-BOX-FOREMAN-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FOREMAN SAYS HIS JAN. 23 BOUT WITH HOLMES IS OFF
</HEADLINE>
  (ms) 
 By TIMOTHY W. SMITH   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   George Foreman is pulling the plug on his Jan. 23 bout against
Larry Holmes. According to Roy Foreman, the former heavyweight
champion's brother, the promoter Roger Leavitt could not secure
financing in a timely manner.
</P>
<P>
   The fight between the aging heavyweights had been in trouble for
some time.
</P>
<P>
   Roy Foreman told The Associated Press Friday that he had
received a call from his brother telling him that the fight was
off. Leavitt was supposed to give letters of credit to both
fighters last week, but did not. He said that he had lost one of
the major financial backers for the fight and needed more time to
find another one. The fighters gave Leavitt another week to come up
with the letters of credit, which he was supposed to provide them
on Thursday. He did not.
</P>
<P>
   Leavitt has already given George Foreman a $1 million advance on
his $10 million purse and has given the 49-year-old Holmes $400,000
of his $4 million purse. Those deposits are nonrefundable.
</P>
<P>
   The fight was planned to coincide with Foreman's 50th birthday
and was supposed to be held in Foreman's hometown, Houston, at the
Astrodome. It was also supposed to be broadcast on pay per view by
Viewer's Choice. However, once Mike Tyson regained his boxing
license after having been suspended for biting Evander Holyfield
during their 1997 bout and chose Jan. 16 as his comeback date,
Foreman-Holmes became a dicey proposition.
</P>
<P>
   It seems unlikely that another promoter will step in to save the
fight, because of the large purses that each fighter has been
guaranteed.
</P>
<P>
   Foreman (76-5) became the oldest heavyweight champion when he
regained the World Boxing Association title at age 45 by knocking
out Michael Moorer in 1994. In his last fight, Foreman lost a
controversial split decision to Shannon Briggs in 1997. Holmes'
record is 66-6.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
